reviews.text: Hi! Aughton Park is on the Ormskirk-Liverpool Central Line on the Northern Line Of Merseyrails Network. It’s basically unstaffed. There is no ticket hall or  a ticket thing like Kirkdale station is. I love the station and I love the classic sign at Street level. It may look grim, but it’s somewhat nice

This railway station is part of the electric Ormskirk to Liverpool line. It has a kiosk for people to buy tickets. No toilets that I'm aware of. Ramps lead down to the platform making it wheelchair accessible.
